Sentencas: The effect of parameters for composite powder preparation on the electrochemical performance of cathodes using mechanically prepared LSM/ScSZ cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells was evaluated.
Titulo: Effect of process parameters on electrochemical properties of mechanically prepared composite powders for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It revealed that the input process energy, which is defined as a time integration of required power for rotor blade driving, consistently described changes in the BET surface area and particle size distribution for composite powder material.
Titulo: Effect of process parameters on electrochemical properties of mechanically prepared composite powders for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Depending on the composite powder samples, however, bulk and interfacial resistances for a half-cell test sample varied in a more complex manner when the input process energy was changed.
Titulo: Effect of process parameters on electrochemical properties of mechanically prepared composite powders for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The present results indicated the importance of process parameters such as the input energy besides the absolute values and ratio of particle size for starting powders and the LSM/ScSZ composition ratio.
Titulo: Effect of process parameters on electrochemical properties of mechanically prepared composite powders for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It can be expected that the electrochemical performance may be further improved with precise matching and controlling of these parameters.
